# Caddy site block for the KausApp admin (in /etc/caddy/Caddyfile on the droplet).
#
# Served over HTTP (port 80), NOT HTTPS. Why: `tailscale serve` already owns
# :443 on this node's tailnet IP (for hackpixels-droplet.tail5822ec.ts.net), so
# it intercepts every TLS connection to 100.99.99.75:443 and terminates it with
# the .ts.net cert — a custom-domain HTTPS vhost (admin.kausapp.com) can't
# terminate at Caddy there (clients get a TLS internal_error). Port 80 isn't
# intercepted, and the tailnet is WireGuard-encrypted, so plain HTTP is fine.
#
# admin.kausapp.com -> A 100.99.99.75 (DNS-only) -> Caddy :80 -> reverse_proxy to
# the admin service on :8080. Reachable only from the tailnet.

http://admin.kausapp.com {
    reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8800
}
